data.description:
This Victorian home features a large covered front porch, high ceilings, hardwood floors, built-in cabinets and bookshelves and over 2,000sqft to make your own. The formal dining room with pocket doors is both grand & inviting. There is a bonus feature of a very sizable room on the main floor that could be used as an office or additional bedroom. Two living spaces on the main create a welcoming environment. This home is large enough for privacy while maintaining the feeling of cozy living. The dual staircases are unique & functional. Vibrant stained glass window and craftsman style details throughout the home such as the built in bench in the entryway make it feel timeless. The ¾ bath on the main floor includes a shower stall. Kitchen has newer cabinetry & countertops as well as fresh paint, entry to the homes closely located two car detached garage.
Three very nicely sized bedrooms on the second floor create tranquility, hosting built in cabinetry and walk in closets. The master bedroom hosts his and her closets and large windows. 
The walkout basement provides so much additional workspace with multiple rooms that include ample shelving. There is plumbing in the basement for an additional bathroom. Roof replaced in 2016 inspected in 2021. New furnace and industrial high efficiency ac unit installed in 2023. Quick 20 minute commute to Ames. Ten minute drive to Ledges State Park. Located across the street from Trinity Lutheran Church and school. Within walking distance of Sacred Heart.
